<br>
You guys really make me sick. For the longest time monks have been the most desired and most powerful class overall. You can wear some of the best gear(which is plentiful in the high end game), you have some of the best DPS, you have been the most sought after classes in the game. You have a whole array of abilities that all the other classes have drooled over for a while. <br>
<br>
From a purely RPG stand point the monk in EQ is 100% overpowered. Take this into consideration, a monk wears little to no armor at all (or in the case of high end stuff, highly magical gear) as to where a warrior or knight wears a full suit of plate armor. A ranger shoots an arrow at the warrior and allthough it hits the warrior (because its hard to be agile wearing full plate) his armor absorbs alot of the damage and the arrow is deflected. You shoot the same arrow at a monk....he is wearing a leather dong cup and he now has to snatch the arrow or dodge its path (which would be easy to do wearing really light clothing) if by chance the arrow does hit the monk he has nothing to shield his skin and therefor it does near maximim damage. This is how it is in all other &quot;RPGs&quot; and how it should be and will be in EQ soon.<br>
<br>
Secondly, about the &quot;OMG I cant believe they nerfed monks shit.&quot; STFU and play a SK. You guys have dodged the nerf bat (because that is what you do....dodge) for a really long time, as to where the SK has stood there and taken it like a man. We have been nerfed into the ground. Every time we discover a problem that we would like to have rectified we get a nerf bat thrown at us. You have no real claim to bitching and crying, the change will make your AC do what it was always supposed to do....avoid, not mitigate. <br>
<br>
Your role as a puller is not going to be gone, it will add a new dimension of skill that you will have to develope to overcome this nerf. Following along the statements I have wrote before, you have dodged the bat for way to long (as you should do as a monk) and now that it fianlly hit you.....it hurts like hell. Welcome to what you should really be.<br>
<br>
Sincerely,<br>
